---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Motel Performance Audit & Optimization | Motel Coach">
  <!-- 1. Revenue-Recovery Hero -->
  <section class="bg-[#F9F9F8] border-b border-stone-200 py-24">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 grid lg:grid-cols-12 gap-12 items-start">
      <div class="lg:col-span-7 space-y-6">
        <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-5xl font-semibold text-stone-900 tracking-tight text-balance">
          Your Motel is Leaving Money on the Table. We Find Exactly Where.
        </h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-stone-500 leading-relaxed">
          A forensic operational and digital audit for independent motels. We diagnose distribution bottlenecks, bloated staff costs, and hidden P&amp;L leaks to rapidly increase your yield.
        </p>

        <div class="bg-white border-2 border-stone-200 rounded-2xl p-6 shadow-sm">
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-stone-400 mb-2">
            Executive Summary:
          </p>
          <p class="text-sm text-stone-600 leading-relaxed">
            The Motel Coach Performance Audit is a comprehensive diagnostic service for Australian independent motels. It identifies operational inefficiencies and OTA distribution errors, delivering a strategic roadmap to increase RevPAR and reduce staff turnover.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="lg:col-span-5">
        <div class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-2xl p-6 shadow-sm space-y-4">
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-stone-400">
            Confidence Metrics
          </p>
          <div class="space-y-3 text-sm text-stone-700">
            <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between">
              <span class="text-stone-500">Properties managed</span>
              <span class="font-semibold text-stone-900">16+</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between">
              <span class="text-stone-500">Regional &amp; metro coverage</span>
              <span class="font-semibold text-stone-900">Specialists</span>
            </div>
            <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between">
              <span class="text-stone-500">Focus</span>
              <span class="font-semibold text-stone-900">Immediate ROI</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 2. Diagnostic Pillars -->
  <section class="bg-white py-24">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6">
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold text-stone-900 tracking-tight text-balance mb-10">
        Diagnostic Pillars
      </h2>
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-6">
        <div class="bg-white border border-stone-200 p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-sm">
          <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between mb-3">
            <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-stone-400">01</p>
            <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-stone-400">OTA &amp; Distribution</p>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-stone-500 leading-relaxed">
            Uncovering rate parity errors, reducing Booking.com reliance, and optimizing channel manager configurations to drive direct bookings.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-stone-200 p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-sm">
          <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between mb-3">
            <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-stone-400">02</p>
            <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-stone-400">Operations &amp; Staffing</p>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-stone-500 leading-relaxed">
            Analyzing housekeeping metrics, front desk workflows, and roster structures to eliminate wasted wage spend.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-stone-200 p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-sm">
          <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between mb-3">
            <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-stone-400">03</p>
            <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-stone-400">Revenue &amp; Pricing</p>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-stone-500 leading-relaxed">
            Evaluating your dynamic pricing strategy and identifying missed yield opportunities during peak and shoulder seasons.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-white border border-stone-200 p-8 rounded-2xl shadow-sm">
          <div class="flex items-baseline justify-between mb-3">
            <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-stone-400">04</p>
            <p class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-stone-400">Digital Health &amp; SEO</p>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-stone-500 leading-relaxed">
            Auditing your Google Business Profile, local ranking factors, and website conversion speed (INP) to capture zero-click search traffic.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 3. Institutional Inquiry Form -->
  <section class="bg-[#F9F9F8] py-24 border-y border-stone-200">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
      <div class="bg-white border border-stone-200 rounded-2xl shadow-sm p-8 md:p-10">
        <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold text-stone-900 tracking-tight mb-2 text-balance">
          Request a Motel Performance Audit
        </h2>
        <p class="text-stone-500 leading-relaxed mb-8">
          Provide a few details below. We&apos;ll review your current operation and respond with the next best step for a confidential performance audit.
        </p>

        <form class="space-y-5" action="https://hooks.zapier.com/hooks/catch/26131104/upwyerc/" method="POST">
          <input type="hidden" name="source_page" value="Operational Performance Audit" />
          <input type="hidden" name="form_type" value="performance-audit" />
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
            <div>
              <label class="block text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-stone-400 mb-1" for="fullName">
                Full Name
              </label>
              <input
                id="fullName"
                name="name"
                type="text"
                required
                class="w-full px-4 py-2.5 rounded-lg border border-stone-200 bg-white text-sm text-stone-900 placeholder-stone-400 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-[#4A554E] focus:border-transparent"
                placeholder="Your name"
              />
            </div>
            <div>
              <label class="block text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-stone-400 mb-1" for="email">
                Email
              </label>
              <input
                id="email"
                name="email"
                type="email"
                required
                class="w-full px-4 py-2.5 rounded-lg border border-stone-200 bg-white text-sm text-stone-900 placeholder-stone-400 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-[#4A554E] focus:border-transparent"
                placeholder="you@example.com"
              />
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
            <div>
              <label class="block text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-stone-400 mb-1" for="phone">
                Phone
              </label>
              <input
                id="phone"
                name="phone"
                type="tel"
                class="w-full px-4 py-2.5 rounded-lg border border-stone-200 bg-white text-sm text-stone-900 placeholder-stone-400 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-[#4A554E] focus:border-transparent"
                placeholder="+61..."
              />
            </div>
            <div>
              <label class="block text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-stone-400 mb-1" for="motelName">
                Motel Name / Location
              </label>
              <input
                id="motelName"
                name="motel_name"
                type="text"
                required
                class="w-full px-4 py-2.5 rounded-lg border border-stone-200 bg-white text-sm text-stone-900 placeholder-stone-400 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-[#4A554E] focus:border-transparent"
                placeholder="e.g. 24-room highway motel in QLD"
              />
            </div>
          </div>

          <div>
            <label class="block text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-stone-400 mb-1" for="pms">
              Current Property Management System (PMS)
            </label>
            <input
              id="pms"
              name="pms"
              type="text"
              class="w-full px-4 py-2.5 rounded-lg border border-stone-200 bg-white text-sm text-stone-900 placeholder-stone-400 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-[#4A554E] focus:border-transparent"
              placeholder="e.g. GuestPoint, RMS, Little Hotelier..."
            />
          </div>

          <div>
            <label class="block text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-stone-400 mb-1" for="frustration">
              What is your primary operational frustration right now?
            </label>
            <textarea
              id="frustration"
              name="frustration"
              rows="4"
              class="w-full px-4 py-2.5 rounded-lg border border-stone-200 bg-white text-sm text-stone-900 placeholder-stone-400 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-[#4A554E] focus:border-transparent"
              placeholder="Tell us what is leaking margin right now: OTA mix, wages, rostering, reviews, pricing, systems, or something else."
            ></textarea>
          </div>

          <button
            type="submit"
            class="w-full inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 px-6 py-3.5 bg-[#4A554E] text-white text-sm font-medium rounded-lg hover:bg-[#3d4640] transition-colors shadow-sm"
          >
            Request Confidential Performance Audit
          </button>

          <p class="mt-3 flex items-center gap-2 text-[11px] text-stone-400">
            <span class="inline-flex h-4 w-4 items-center justify-center rounded-full border border-stone-300 text-[9px]">🔒</span>
            <span>All inquiries are handled with 100% practitioner–client confidentiality.</span>
          </p>
        </form>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- 4. Benjamin Douglas Bio Snippet -->
  <section class="bg-white py-20">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-6 border-t border-stone-200 pt-10">
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-12 gap-10 items-start">
        <div class="md:col-span-4">
          <h2 class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest text-stone-400 mb-3">
            Why Benjamin Douglas?
          </h2>
          <p class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-semibold text-stone-900 tracking-tight text-balance">
            Practitioner-led diagnostics for serious motel operators.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="md:col-span-8 space-y-3 text-sm text-stone-500 leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            Benjamin Douglas is the Lead Practitioner at Motel Coach and author of <em>The Essential Guide to Motel Management</em>.
            He has overseen operations across 16+ motels, 10 restaurants, and over 200 staff.
            This audit service is not a generic corporate report—it is a precise, practitioner-led diagnostic grounded in years of frontline turnaround experience.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

